sql:
SELECT AVG(duration) AS average_game_duration
FROM games
WHERE game_mode = 'competitive' AND winner IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
- "longest-lasting games" refers to games that lasted more than 1 hour (3600 seconds);
- "victor's reputation shines brightly" refers to the average rating of the winner;
- "battles waged beyond the hour mark" refers to the duration of the game sessions being greater than 3600 seconds;
- "the grandest tales of triumph being the most recent" refers to the games being ordered by start time in descending order and limited to the top 10.

- Active players are those whose `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- The `game_id` uniquely identifies each game session;
- The `rating` is a score given by players, ranging from 1 to 5.

sql:
SELECT AVG(g.duration) AS average_duration
FROM games g
INNER JOIN feedback f ON g.game_id = f.game_id;

